Health & Safety Manager
03 May 2014 06:44 AM - UAE
.
The Health & Safety Manager role is accountable for the people leadership of their team and for ensuring that Health & Safety policies and procedures are effectively embedded across projects, sites and office environments in compliance with local and international rules and regulations. The role holder must take a 'hands on' approach to all aspects of the role.
Responsibilities
Business Leadership• Responsible for the leadership and support of their team• Ensure that Health & Safety is embedded into all work practices in line with company policies• Ensure the right resources are utilised effectively at the right time across their team and projects• Input into the recruitment and selection process• Conduct meaningful inductions, performance management reviews and personal development plans that support the development of individuals and the business• Contribute to succession planning and career development across their team• Support the development and delivery of training and awareness sessions as required• Contribute to the development and implementation of the business unit (BU) strategy• Provide project and team updates for the development of the Operational Leadership Team (OLT) monthly reports• Attend and lead team and project meetings, cascade relevant information and encourage feedback from team• Input into setting and delivering P&L BU budget and forecasts• Lead by example and ensure QMS and Project Lifecycle compliance across their team and projects.• Provide guidance and support the companies approach to Sustainability and ensure that the Sustainability strategy is implemented across teamBusiness Development• Contribute to business development activities through participation in external market profile raising activities and functions• Actively develop external and internal client relationships• Proactively co sell other WSP ME services and where applicable the wider business• Contribute to the Key Account Management (KAM) programmes, with the aim of increasing client intelligence to develop win solutions and support unique selling points for prospects.• Provide technical leadership to respond to prequalification documents, Request for Price (RFPs) and other client inquiries• Contribute to the financial build-up of resources and lump sum pricing items for prospects where requiredProject Leadership• To act as PM on selected projects by managing the successful delivery of high quality multi and single disciplinary projects• Ensure that own projects adhere to Project Lifecycle and that projects led by direct reports adhere to Project Lifecycle• Support the formation of the contractual relationship between the business and the client; taking the process from proposal to contract, utilising the advice of the support functions• Engage with the CRCs at the Prospect stage through to completion to ensure the most cost efficient delivery of their projects.• Ensure proactive project planning, stakeholder and risk management takes place across projects• Supervise the team to identify, assess and manage major project risk and secure the best commercial return from the projects in their portfolio• To ensure statutory and regulatory requirements are met• Support the delivery of project P&L budgets, forecasts and working capital targets for own projects and projects led by direct reports• Support the accurate and timely recognition of revenue for own projects and projects led by direct reports• Support the overseeing and delivery of the process of working capital management from inception to completion within set deadlines; This includes the timing of invoicing, the review of Work in Progress (WIP) and the collection of outstanding invoices from clients whilst utilising the advice of the support functions as necessary• Contribute to the completion of monthly management project reports to be issued by set deadlineTechnical• Conduct and oversee audits and reviews of the environment, practices and behaviors across site and offices• Lead the development of policies and review compliance as required• Provide advice and guidance on all aspects of Health & Safety on site and in the office environment• Analyse statistics of all accidents, near misses, dangerous occurrence, with the view of making recommendations Lead the investigation and close out of all safety actions for investigations or inspections • Issue safety notice for unsafe work and follow through for immediate rectification• Prepare and submit Health & Safety reports to the client as required• Provide support and guidance to Technical Working Group (TWG)• Keep up to date with industry developments with respect to own discipline and understand and appreciate the basic technical principles and drivers of other disciplines• Develop the capabilities of direct reports
Requirements
• Degree qualified with a minimum 15 years post graduate experience• Chartered Member of associated Professional body or Member giving eligibility to become Chartered• Regional Ex (more...)
